# Editorial Style

Full detail: `.playbook/05_STYLE_GUIDE.md`.

- Professional, timeless, vendor-neutral where possible, actionable, concise but complete. Active voice. Lead with
  the point.
- Mark verified facts distinctly from opinion/inference — phrase inference explicitly ("likely uses," "publicly
  unconfirmed") rather than as fact.
- Headings sentence case. Numbered lists for sequences, bullets for unordered collections. Tables for anything
  with more than 3 comparable attributes per item.
- Don't introduce a new term for a concept that already has an entry in `05_STYLE_GUIDE.md`'s terminology table
  (e.g. "Adobe Experience Manager (AEM)" not "Adobe AEM").
- Don't pad a section to look thorough without adding information density.
